The cell temperature is calculated in the SAPM by using the ambient dry bulb temperature Ta in ∘C, the plane of array effective irradiance Itr in W/m2 and the wind speed WS in m/s at a height of 10 meters, in order to include heating effects from the sun and cooling effects from the wind. The cell temperature is calculated in (4) and the back-surface module temperature Tm is defined in (5). 
